Pittman was born in Glasgow and started his career at Rangers, where he was a regular in the youth team. He was released by Rangers in 2006 and joined Livingston in 2007.

Midsomer Norton is a town and civil parish in the unitary authority of Bath and North East Somerset and the ceremonial county of Somerset, England. It is situated on the River Frome, 3 miles (5 km) south of Bath and 5 miles (8 km) north of Radstock. The population of the civil parish at the 2011 Census was 16,000.
The town is the administrative centre of the Midsomer Norton and Radstock constituency

The 2008 Ryder Cup was the 37th edition of the Ryder Cup, a biennial golf competition contested by teams from Europe and the United States. It was held at Valhalla Golf Club in Louisville, Kentucky, United States, from 18 to 20 September 2008. The European team, captained by Nick Faldo, won the competition for the first time since 1995.
The European team was led by Faldo, who was making his second appearance as captain. The team was made up of Padraig Harrington, Ian Poulter, Henrik Stenson, Sergio García, Paul Casey, Miguel Ángel Jiménez, and Ross Fisher. The team was the first to feature four players from the top 10 in the Official World Golf Ranking.

Catalan: <s>Almanac: El inventor del contador Geiger</s>
French: <s>Almanac: L'inventeur du compteur Geiger</s>

Portuguese: <s>Almanac: O inventor do contador Geiger</s>
Spanish: <s>Almanac: El inventor del contador Geiger</s>
Categories: 1910 births | 1990 deaths | German inventors | German scientists | Nobel Prize in Physics winners | People from Berlin | People from Germany | Physicists | Radiology pioneers
Alfred Werner (February 28, 1910 – December 1, 1990) was a German physicist and Nobel Prize winner.
Werner was born in Berlin, Germany. He studied physics at the University of Berlin, where he received his doctorate in 1933. He then worked at the Kaiser Wilhelm Institute for Physical Chemistry and Electrochemistry in Berlin. In 1938, he was appointed professor of physical chemistry at the University of Berlin.

Kanye West is a rapper, singer, songwriter, record producer, and entrepreneur. He is known for his controversial statements and his eccentric fashion sense.
Contents
- 1 Early life
- 2 Career
- 3 Personal life
- 4 Controversies
- 5 Discography
- 6 Awards and nominations
- 7 References
- 8 External links
Early life
Kanye Omari West was born on June 8, 1977, in Atlanta, Georgia, to Ray West and Donda West. He was raised in Chicago, Illinois, and attended Chicago State University. He was raised in a strict Christian household, and his mother was a gospel singer. He has two younger sisters, Kaela and LaShondra, and a younger brother, Russell.

This is a stub. You can help by expanding it.
Big if true (BIT) is a phrase used to describe a claim that is true if it is true, but false if it is false. It is a logical fallacy, and is often used to describe a claim that is true, but is not true.
The phrase is often used in the context of a claim that is true, but is not true. For example, if a person says that the sky is blue, and it is not true, then the person is saying that the sky is not blue.
The phrase is also used to describe a claim that is true, but is not true. For example, if a person says that the sky is blue, and it is not true, then the person is saying that the sky is not blue.

The 2018 Ryder Cup is set to be the 42nd edition of the Ryder Cup, a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. The event will be held at Le Golf National in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France, from September 28 to October 1, 2018.

Catalan: <s>2006: A 6.8 magnitude hit south of Java, Indonesia's most populated island, triggering a tsunami that smashed into the southern coast, killing nearly 700 people.</s>
The 2006 Java earthquake and tsunami was a major earthquake and tsunami that occurred on 27 December 2006, at 00:58:53 UTC (19:58:53 local time), with a magnitude of 6.8 and a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe). The earthquake was centered 100 km (62 mi) south of the city of Yogyakarta, Indonesia, and 200 km (120 mi) south of the city of Surabaya, Indonesia. The earthquake was felt as far away as Singapore, Malaysia, and the Philippines.
The earthquake was the deadliest natural disaster in Indonesia since the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami. The earthquake and tsunami killed 5,000 people, and injured 1,000 more. The earthquake also caused $1.5 billion in damage.

English: <s>2018: Major quakes hit Indonesia's tourist island of Lombok, killing more than 500 people, mostly on the northern side of the island.</s>
Catalan: <s>2018: Major quakes hit Indonesia's tourist island of Lombok, killing more than 500 people, mostly on the northern side of the island.</s>
The 2018 Lombok earthquake was a series of earthquakes that occurred on the island of Lombok, Indonesia, on 5 and 6 August 2018. The earthquakes were centered on Lombok, with the epicenters located 6 km (3.7 mi) north of the town of Senggigi and 7 km (4.3 mi) north of the town of Mataram. The earthquakes were felt as far away as Bali, 100 km (62 mi) to the south, and as far away as Singapore, 1,000 km (620 mi) to the east.
The earthquakes were the deadliest earthquakes to hit Indonesia since the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami, which killed 230,000 people. The earthquakes killed at least 460 people, with 1,000 injured and 100,000 displaced. The earthquakes caused widespread damage to buildings, roads, and bridges, and destroyed 1,000 homes.

The Ryder Cup is a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. The competition is named after Samuel Ryder, a British businessman who founded the competition in 1927.
The Ryder Cup is played every two years, alternating between the United States and Europe. The competition is played over three days, with 12 players on each team. The competition is played in a match play format, with each player playing against each other player on the opposing team. The team with the most points at the end of the competition wins.
The Ryder Cup is one of the most prestigious golf competitions in the world. It is also one of the most watched sporting events in the world. The competition is broadcast live on television in many countries.

The 2018 Ryder Cup was the 42nd edition of the Ryder Cup, a biennial golf competition contested by teams from Europe and the United States. It was held from 28 September to 30 September 2018 at Le Golf National in Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines, France.
The European team, captained by Thomas Bjørn, defeated the United States team, captained by Jim Furyk, by a score of 16.5 to 10.5. This was the first time since 2008 that the European team had won the Ryder Cup.

The 2012 Ryder Cup was the 39th Ryder Cup, a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. It was held at the Medinah Country Club in Medinah, Illinois, United States, from 28–30 September 2012. The United States team, captained by Davis Love III, defeated the European team, captained by José María Olazábal, by a score of 14½–13½.
The United States team was composed of Tiger Woods, Phil Mickelson, Steve Stricker, Matt Kuchar, Dustin Johnson, Webb Simpson, Jason Dufner, Zach Johnson, and rookie Jordan Spieth. The European team was composed of Rory McIlroy, Ian Poulter, Justin Rose, Graeme McDowell, Sergio García, Luke Donald, Lee Westwood, Peter Hanson, and rookie Jamie Donaldson.

About[edit]
The phrase "Hats off to you!" is a common expression of praise, used to congratulate someone on a job well done. It is often used in the context of a sporting event, such as a race, a game, or a match.
